               <head>Kashf al-maḥjūb by Hujvīrī</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh85129660 https://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2008112367">
                  <summary>The well-known treatise on Sufism, <title>Kashf al-maḥjūb</title>, composed in the 11th century CE by ʻAlī ibn Us̱mān Hujvīrī. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <author key="person_166217879">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">ʻAlī ibn Us̱mān Hujvīrī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">علی بن عثمان هجویری</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23287">Kashf al-maḥjūb</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23287">کشف المحجوب</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">ربنا آتنا من لدنک رحمته و هی لنا من امرنا رشدا. الحمد لله الذی کشف الاولیاء بواطن ملکوته الخ.</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">و اندر حکایات مشهور است که جنید و محمد بن مسروق</explicit>
                     <note>
                        <p>On <locus n="1v">f. 1v</locus>, the author's name is misspelt as Ḥujvīrī. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <extent>ff. i+340 + wrapper<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>260</height>
